Cooperation between the two Court of Auditors
In the run-up to the parallel audit, several meetings of representatives of both Court of Auditors took place.
Participants at these meetings familiarized themselves with the organization of the tax administration, the legislation on VAT and the system of VAT administration in the other country.
The subject of the test phase was agreed at the meeting in May 2006.
The results of the test phase were evaluated at the next joint meeting in August 2006.
At this meeting, a timetable for the further procedure was drawn up and the following examinations were identified for the parallel examinations: 1.
Registration of tax payers.
2.
Cross-border passenger transport by coach and coach — legislation in the Czech Republic and Germany.
3. International exchange of information, in particular the actions of financial officials in dealing with requests for information and the review of selected problem cases mentioned in the requests for information, as well as spontaneous information between the Czech Republic and Germany.
4. Tax returns.
5.
Summary messages.
6.
Statistical information on deliveries and purchases between the Czech Republic and Germany.
7. Risk management in the VAT area.
At a meeting to vote on the further examination of the NKÚ and the BRH in December 2006, both sides familiarized themselves with the examination procedure in the Czech Republic and Germany and discussed the results of the parallel tests already achieved.
