8 of the information in the CM with which The Tax Permit corrects incorrect information in the CM by submitting a correction IMM either on his own initiative or upon request.
The financial officer shall correct the data on deliveries of goods to other Member States in the ATIS system if:
— the taxpayer does not prove the correctness of the information reported in the ATM (or correction) and therefore corrects it by submitting a correction IM,
— the financial officer has demonstrated the inaccuracy of the information reported by the taxpayer in the ATM or correction ATM.
Adjustments entered by the tax officer, without the filing of a correction by the taxpayer, do not replace the duty of the taxpayer to submit a correction, but only result in the correction of the data in the MIAS, so that these are current, complete and accurate.
Data from the ZM shall be forwarded to the Member States concerned.
Only the national tax authority designated for cooperation with the other Member States in the field of turnover tax may transmit and receive such data.
This is the CLO (in the Czech Republic this function is performed by the Department of International Administrative Assistance in the field of VAT in the Ministry of Finance). The “O_MCTL” message is automatically sent to the CLO from the other Member States.
It contains all incorrect VAT IDs that were specified in the submitted CM lines.
If the incorrect VAT ID number is used in some of the submitted lines of the ZM or the corrected ZM, an entry is made in the list of the incorrect VAT ID number.
The list contains a “notification of doubts concerning VAT number”.
The financial officer checks the data and enters the result of the verification into the system.
In the case of purchase of goods from another Member State, the taxpayer shall indicate this in his VAT return and enter the value of the purchase in the lines of the VAT return for that purpose.
Selected cases of differences between the values of the acquisitions made by the Czech taxpayer in his VAT return and the values specified by the supplier from the other Member State for the delivery of goods in his VAT return shall be forwarded by the CLO to the competent FA for verification.
The specialists there have to examine the deviations.
There can then be three different situations:
(a) The value indicated by the Czech acquirer in the relevant headings of his VAT return is lower than the value of the supplies indicated by suppliers from other EC Member States.
In this case, the financial officer shall verify the accuracy of the information.
(b) The difference is zero.
This situation may arise either by changing the information within the EC (the foreign supplier corrects its ZM) or by changing the information in the VAT return (the Czech tax person makes a supplementary VAT return on his own initiative).
In this case, it is at the discretion of the tax officer to verify the accuracy of the information in the VAT return anyway.
(c) The value of the goods purchased from other Member States indicated by the Czech taxpayer in his VAT return is higher than the values of their deliveries reported by the suppliers of the other EC Member States.
Here, in turn, it is at the discretion of the financial officer to verify the accuracy of the information.
After reviewing the differences and clarifying the reasons for their occurrence, the financial officer shall enter the results of his review in ATIS.
These results are forwarded to the CLO.
