International exchange of information at level 3
Implementation of international exchange of information in the Czech Republic
The international exchange of information enables financial officials to obtain information from other Member States on intra-Community transactions and on the taxpayers who have carried out them.
Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 on mutual assistance in the field of surplus value tax, which repeals Directive (EEC) No 218/92 (hereinafter referred to as “Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003”) distinguishes between two basic ways of exchanging information: the exchange of information on request and the spontaneous Exchange of information (without prior request).
International exchange of information upon request shall be carried out by means of a request for information (RFI) using the standardised SCAC form.
Financial officers in the Czech Republic send their RFIs or their replies to a received RFI to the CLO through the Financial Directorate. The latter shall ensure that the information provided in the standardised SCAC form is translated into the foreign language and that it is forwarded to the other Member States.
In addition, the CLO receives requests for information (RFI) from other Member States and replies to requests sent. It takes care of their translation into Czech and their distribution to the competent FÄs for processing.
Article 8 of Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 sets a period not exceeding three months from the date of receipt of the request for its processing.
