By asking the local competent Czech tax officer, the NKÚ found that the Czech tax officer had submitted a supplementary tax return for the fourth quarter of 2004 following a tax audit, declaring, among other things, the value of the goods he had acquired from a German tax agent. and at the same time invoked the right to deduct VAT for the acquisition from other Member States.
In his Czech VAT return, he did not register VAT on the sale of goods in Germany.
On the basis of a supplementary VAT return submitted after the external audit, the Czech tax officer fixed the VAT liability unchanged.
